%N A397291 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k+1) * AH(k,8)/k, where AH(k,8) = Sum_{i=1..k} (-1)^(i+1)/i^8 is the k-th alternating harmonic (or skew-harmonic) number of order 8.
%H A397291 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.22, p. 427.
